-NEWMIE: ALL RIGHT, CLEAR,
HE'S SHOCKABLE.

07:12.649 --> 07:14.042
-[SHOCKING]

07:14.172 --> 07:15.391
-DEFIBRILLATOR:
ANALYZING RHYTHM.

07:15.522 --> 07:16.871
-NEWMIE: STAY CLEAR,
WE'RE GONNA GO AGAIN.

07:17.001 --> 07:18.220
-DEFIBRILLATOR:
STAND CLEAR.

07:18.350 --> 07:20.483
[SHOCKING SOUND]
ANALYZING RHYTHM.

07:20.614 --> 07:22.398
-COME ON, COME ON!

07:25.096 --> 07:27.795
-[SHOCKING SOUND]

07:27.925 --> 07:29.100
-ALL RIGHT,
CHECK HIS PULSE.

07:30.580 --> 07:31.842
-HE'S GOT A PULSE.

07:31.973 --> 07:33.409
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET
A BLOOD PRESSURE ON HIM.

07:36.325 --> 07:41.461
-[BREATHING NOISES]
-[HEART BEATING]

07:43.245 --> 07:45.116
-HEY, NICE JOB YOU TWO.

07:47.858 --> 07:49.120
-READY FOR THE BIG DIVE?

07:49.251 --> 07:50.731
-YEAH, CHECKING
OUT SOME EQUIPMENT.

07:50.861 --> 07:51.949
NEWMIE AND I ARE GOING OUT
WITH SOME OF THE ROOKIES

07:52.080 --> 07:53.560
TO HELP THEM
GET CERTIFIED.

07:53.690 --> 07:54.778
-WHY DO I GET THE
FEELING THAT YOU'RE NEVER

07:54.909 --> 07:55.997
GOING TO PRACTICE
LAW AGAIN?

07:56.127 --> 07:57.520
-BEATS SITTING
IN A COURT ROOM.

07:57.651 --> 07:58.826
-GOT THAT RIGHT. OH,
LISTEN, YOU ARE NOT

07:58.956 --> 07:59.740
ON THE SCHEDULE
TOMORROW BUT I NEED

07:59.870 --> 08:01.132
YOU TO WORK ANYWAY.

08:01.263 --> 08:02.699
-AH, NO, NO, NO,
I CAN'T TOMORROW.

08:02.830 --> 08:04.266
TOMORROW I'M
GOING DIVING.

08:04.396 --> 08:05.789
IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME
SINCE I'VE BEEN DOWN

08:05.920 --> 08:07.356
AND CHECKED OUT THE
FISH COUNTS AND I GOT

08:07.487 --> 08:08.662
THIS GREAT NEW WEBSITE
THAT TELLS ME WHERE

08:08.792 --> 08:10.141
THE NEW MARINE
POPULATIONS ARE.

08:10.272 --> 08:11.491
I'M GONNA GO DOWN
AND CHECK THEM OUT.

08:12.404 --> 08:14.145
WELL, I, I SUPPOSE I
COULD PUSH IT BACK,

08:14.276 --> 08:15.495
BUT JUST A LITTLE BIT.

08:15.625 --> 08:16.713
-HOW FAR?

08:16.844 --> 08:17.409
-WHAT DO YOU
MEAN HOW FAR?

08:17.540 --> 08:19.194
WHAT'S UP?

08:19.324 --> 08:20.761
-I GOT A TRAINING SEMINAR
TO GO TO IN SANTA BARBARA,

08:20.891 --> 08:23.198
I NEED YOU TO HANG AROUND
HERE FOR JUST A COUPLE

08:23.328 --> 08:24.721
OF DAYS AND GIVE
TAYLOR A HAND.

08:24.852 --> 08:26.201
-OKAY, ALL RIGHT, IF
YOU NEED ME I'M THERE.

08:26.331 --> 08:27.115
-GREAT, THANKS.

08:27.245 --> 08:28.029
-YOU'RE WELCOME.

08:28.159 --> 08:28.986
-HEY, HOW'D IT GO?

08:29.117 --> 08:30.379
-HOW DID WHAT GO?

08:30.510 --> 08:31.293
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN
HOW DID WHAT GO?

08:31.423 --> 08:32.033
HOW DID YOUR DATE GO?

08:32.163 --> 08:33.600
-WHAT DATE?

08:33.730 --> 08:34.861
-YOUR DATE, COME ON,
YOU'RE TALKING TO MITCH

08:34.991 --> 08:36.428
NOW AND NOT THE
CAPTAIN, YOUR DATE

08:36.558 --> 08:38.256
WITH THE JAGUAR
LADY, HOW'D IT GO?

08:38.386 --> 08:39.693
-OH, THE JAGUAR LADY?
-YEAH!

08:39.823 --> 08:40.955
-THAT'S TONIGHT.

08:41.085 --> 08:42.304
-OH.
-YEAH.

08:42.433 --> 08:44.174
-OH, WELL, OF COURSE
I EXPECT A FULL

08:44.306 --> 08:46.134
REPORT WHEN I RETURN
FROM SANTA BARBARA.

08:46.264 --> 08:47.222
-YEAH, OF COURSE YOU DO.

08:47.352 --> 08:48.397
-THANKS, TAKE CARE.

08:48.528 --> 08:49.224
-YEAH, YEAH,
YOU'RE WELCOME.

08:49.354 --> 08:51.095
SEE YA.

08:51.226 --> 08:54.272
-[POP MUSIC]

08:57.362 --> 08:58.755
-MANNY!

08:58.886 --> 09:00.235
TURN AROUND, I WANT
TO GET YOUR PICTURE.

09:00.365 --> 09:01.410
-MOM!

09:01.541 --> 09:03.717
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

09:03.847 --> 09:05.283
I THOUGHT YOU
HAD TO WORK?

09:05.414 --> 09:06.589
-WELL, I TOOK
THE DAY OFF.

09:06.720 --> 09:08.722
I WANTED TO SEE
MY SON AT HIS JOB.

09:08.852 --> 09:10.419
THAT'S MY SON,
THE LIFEGUARD.

09:10.550 --> 09:11.725
-MOM, STOP THAT.

09:11.855 --> 09:14.336
-WELL CAN'T A MOTHER
BE PROUD OF HER SON?

09:14.466 --> 09:15.946
NOW, COME ON, GIVE
ME A SMILE AND

09:16.077 --> 09:18.209
HOLD ONTO THAT, THAT
BUOY THING OVER THERE.

09:18.906 --> 09:20.647
-MOM, THAT'S NOT
A BUOY THING,

09:20.777 --> 09:22.518
IT'S A RESCUE CAN.

09:25.608 --> 09:27.784
-OH, YOU'RE SO HANDSOME.

09:27.915 --> 09:29.786
-[MANNY LAUGHS]
-LIFEGUARD: HEY, MANNY!

09:30.526 --> 09:31.440
-HI!

09:34.399 --> 09:35.749
-OH, IS THAT HER?

09:35.879 --> 09:36.750
IS THAT THE
NEW GIRLFRIEND?

09:37.707 --> 09:39.404
SHE LOOKS
LIKE A NICE GIRL.

09:39.535 --> 09:41.189
-MOM, THAT'S NOT HER.

09:41.885 --> 09:44.105
-WELL WHEN DO I GET
A CHANCE TO MEET HER?

09:44.235 --> 09:46.890
-LATER, I HAVE
TO WORK RIGHT NOW.

09:47.630 --> 09:49.110
-WELL, OKAY, MIJO
YOU DO YOUR WORK,

09:49.240 --> 09:52.461
YOU KNOW, JUST PRETEND
THAT I'M NOT HERE, OKAY?

09:53.897 --> 09:57.858
-[POP MUSIC]

10:07.519 --> 10:08.303
-HI CRAIG.

10:08.433 --> 10:09.304
-HEY!

10:09.870 --> 10:10.784
I HEARD YOU HAD
SOME EXCITEMENT ON

10:10.914 --> 10:12.524
THE BEACH THIS MORNING.

10:12.655 --> 10:14.265
-YEAH, A LITTLE BOY GOT
SWEPT OUT ON THE RIP CURRENT.

10:14.396 --> 10:16.311
FOR SOME REASON THEY'RE
REALLY STRONG TODAY.

10:16.441 --> 10:18.095
-THE STORM LAST WEEK CHANGED
THE BOTTOM ALL AROUND.

10:18.226 --> 10:20.837
-WELL, I'M STILL
LEARNING ABOUT THE OCEAN.

10:20.968 --> 10:22.926
-ME, TOO, IT'S A BIG OCEAN,
THERE'S A LOT TO LEARN.

10:23.057 --> 10:24.014
-SO MANNY SAYS
YOU'RE HELPING SOME OF

10:24.145 --> 10:25.189
THE LIFEGUARDS
GET CERTIFIED.

10:25.320 --> 10:26.495
-MM-HMM.

10:26.626 --> 10:27.496
-HE'S REALLY
EXCITED ABOUT IT.

10:27.627 --> 10:28.845
-GOOD, YOU INTERESTED?

10:28.976 --> 10:30.542
-ACTUALLY I'M
ALREADY CERTIFIED.

10:30.673 --> 10:31.935
IT WAS ONE OF THE FIRST
THINGS I DID WHEN I CAME

10:32.066 --> 10:34.242
TO CALIFORNIA.
I LOVE DIVING.

10:34.982 --> 10:36.679
-MAYBE WE CAN
GO OUT SOME TIME.

10:37.680 --> 10:39.900
I MEAN, YOU
KNOW, DIVING.

10:40.944 --> 10:42.337
-I'D LOVE TO.

10:42.467 --> 10:43.686
IF YOU EVER NEED A BUDDY
JUST GIVE ME A CALL.

10:43.817 --> 10:45.035
-I WILL.

10:45.166 --> 10:45.601
-I'M GONNA GET
BACK TO THE TOWER.

10:45.732 --> 10:46.471
-WANT A LIFT?

10:46.602 --> 10:47.385
-SURE.

10:47.516 --> 10:48.560
-HOP IN.

10:52.173 --> 10:53.174
-APRIL: THANKS
FOR THE RIDE.

10:53.304 --> 10:54.436
-CRAIG: ANY TIME.

10:55.176 --> 10:56.264
-DON'T FORGET TO
GIVE ME A CALL,

10:56.394 --> 10:57.308
WE'LL GO OUT.

10:57.439 --> 10:58.570
-DIVING.

11:01.095 --> 11:05.969
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

11:21.245 --> 11:22.420
-WOMAN: WAIT
UP YOU GUYS!

11:28.165 --> 11:29.863
-SO THE LITTLE
BOY'S GONNA BE OKAY.

11:29.993 --> 11:31.429
HE JUST HAD A
HECK OF A SCARE.

11:31.560 --> 11:33.257
HIS MOTHER CAME
AND GOT HIM.

11:33.910 --> 11:34.868
-HMM.

11:36.260 --> 11:37.871
-YOU KNOW, I TOLD
HER THAT HE SWALLOWED

11:38.001 --> 11:39.568
A LOT OF WATER WHICH
CAN SOMETIMES CAUSE

11:39.699 --> 11:41.178
SECONDARY DROWNING.

11:42.527 --> 11:44.138
-YEAH, THAT'S,
THAT'S GREAT.

11:45.269 --> 11:47.141
-MANNY, ARE YOU
LISTENING TO ME?

11:47.271 --> 11:48.229
-BOY: WAIT UP!

11:48.838 --> 11:49.752
-BOY 2: HERE,
RIGHT HERE.

11:50.361 --> 11:51.362
-MANNY: HEY!
-MANNY!

11:51.493 --> 11:52.886
-MANNY: HEY,
YOU GUYS!

11:53.016 --> 11:54.365
I'M SORRY, WAIT A
MINUTE, WAIT A MINUTE!

11:54.496 --> 11:55.410
HEY!

11:57.368 --> 11:58.935
HEY, LISTEN TO ME!

12:00.676 --> 12:02.112
-WHAT'S HE DOING?

12:03.026 --> 12:04.462
-WELL YOU'RE NOT ALLOWED
TO TAKE INNER TUBES

12:04.593 --> 12:05.550
OUT INTO THE WATER.

12:05.681 --> 12:06.464
-OH, REALLY?

12:06.595 --> 12:07.814
WHY IS THAT?

12:07.944 --> 12:09.816
-WELL, IT'S DANGEROUS
WHEN THE SURF IS HEAVY.

12:10.817 --> 12:13.471
-OH, NO WONDER HE
TOOK OFF SO FAST.

12:13.602 --> 12:14.864
I'M MANNY'S MOTHER.

12:16.257 --> 12:17.127
-REALLY?

12:17.258 --> 12:18.346
HIS MOTHER?

12:18.476 --> 12:19.782
-TERESA GUTTIEREZ.

12:19.913 --> 12:21.523
-GOSH, I'VE HEARD
SO MUCH ABOUT YOU.

12:21.653 --> 12:23.394
IT'S NICE TO FINALLY
MEET YOU, I'M APRIL.

12:24.700 --> 12:25.919
APRIL GAMINSKI?

12:26.484 --> 12:28.356
-YOU KNOW, BECOMING A
LIFEGUARD WAS PROBABLY

12:28.486 --> 12:30.314
THE BEST THING THAT
EVER HAPPENED TO MANUEL,

12:30.445 --> 12:32.403
IT OPENED UP A WHOLE
NEW WORLD FOR HIM.

12:32.969 --> 12:34.536
-ME, TOO.

12:34.666 --> 12:35.885
-YOU KNOW THAT'S ALL
HE TALKS ABOUT WHEN

12:36.016 --> 12:37.495
HE COMES HOME AT NIGHT,
HE SAYS WHAT HE DID

12:37.626 --> 12:39.280
ON THE BEACH SO I FINALLY
DECIDED TO COME AND

12:39.410 --> 12:41.064
SEE FOR MYSELF.

12:42.718 --> 12:44.633
-I'M SORRY, WOULD
YOU EXCUSE ME?

12:44.764 --> 12:47.810
-OH, SURE, I KNOW THAT
YOU HAVE A JOB TO DO, TOO?

12:47.941 --> 12:50.378
MY SON CAN'T BE THE ONLY
ONE WATCHING THIS BEACH.

12:50.508 --> 12:51.901
IT WAS NICE TO
MEET YOU, APRIL.

12:52.032 --> 12:53.294
-YOU, TOO.

13:05.175 --> 13:07.090
MANNY, DO YOU HAVE SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO TELL ME?

13:07.221 --> 13:08.613
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

13:08.744 --> 13:11.138
-OH, I DON'T KNOW, MAYBE
LIKE WHY YOUR MOTHER

13:11.268 --> 13:13.314
IS STANDING ON THE BEACH AND
YOU FORGOT TO MENTION IT?

13:13.444 --> 13:15.751
-LOOK, THOSE BOYS HAD
INNER TUBES IN THE WATER,

13:15.882 --> 13:17.361
I HAD TO GO AND
GET THEM OUT.

13:19.015 --> 13:21.626
-MANNY, SHE HAS
NO IDEA WHO I AM.

13:22.279 --> 13:24.020
HAVE YOU NOT EVEN
TOLD HER ABOUT ME?

13:24.151 --> 13:25.935
-OF COURSE I DID.

13:26.066 --> 13:28.111
-OH, BUT JUST NOT MY NAME
OR WHAT I LOOK LIKE, RIGHT?

13:32.246 --> 13:34.683
WHAT I LOOK LIKE, THAT'S
WHAT THIS IS ABOUT, ISN'T IT?

13:35.510 --> 13:37.120
-APRIL, YOU
DON'T UNDERSTAND.

13:37.773 --> 13:39.383
-OH, I UNDERSTAND
ALL RIGHT.

13:39.514 --> 13:40.994
YOU'RE ASHAMED OF ME
AND YOU DON'T WANT

13:41.124 --> 13:42.822
ANYBODY TO KNOW ABOUT ME.

13:42.952 --> 13:45.085
-THAT'S NOT TRUE,
I NEVER SAID THAT.

13:46.086 --> 13:47.827
-YES, MANNY, YOU DID.

13:49.350 --> 13:53.093
-[DRAMATIC ACOUSTIC MUSIC]

13:57.619 --> 14:01.057
-[DRAMATIC ACOUSTIC MUSIC]

14:18.466 --> 14:19.946
-TAYLOR: HEY, YOU
NEED A LIFT?

14:20.947 --> 14:22.339
-WE HAVE OUR CAR HERE.

14:22.470 --> 14:24.167
HI, I'M MANNY'S MOTHER.

14:24.298 --> 14:26.691
-HI, MRS. GUTTIEREZ,
I'M LIEUTENANT WALSH.

14:26.822 --> 14:28.780
YOUR SON'S DOING
A REAL FINE JOB.

14:28.911 --> 14:31.174
WE'RE REALLY GLAD TO HAVE
HIM HERE AT BAYWATCH.

14:31.305 --> 14:32.959
-CAN I GET A PICTURE
OF HIM WITH THE BOSS?

14:34.047 --> 14:35.265
MANNY?

14:36.745 --> 14:38.921
-JUST A SEC, MOM,
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

14:39.052 --> 14:41.271
-HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

14:41.402 --> 14:44.492
I HAVE SOME PHOTOS
FROM THE CAMP BAYWATCH

14:44.622 --> 14:48.888
BARBECUE FROM LAST WEEK.
MANNY'S IN A FEW OF THESE.

14:49.018 --> 14:51.194
YOU COULD HAVE
THEM IF YOU'D LIKE.

14:51.325 --> 14:54.545
-[LAUGHING] OH THEY LOOK LIKE
THEY HAD A WONDERFUL TIME.

14:54.676 --> 14:55.851
-YEAH.

14:56.721 --> 14:58.158
-[TERESA LAUGHS]

15:03.250 --> 15:04.120
-MAY I HAVE THIS ONE?

