-CALL SCARAB ONE, GIVE THEM
THE NEW SEARCH COORDINATES.

32:36.171 --> 32:37.825
-YOU GOT IT.

32:37.956 --> 32:39.348
-DISPATCH: SCARAB ONE,
THIS IS BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS,

32:39.479 --> 32:41.046
PROCEED TWO MILES
NORTH NORTHWEST

32:41.176 --> 32:42.786
OF PALOS VERDES PENINSULA.

32:46.138 --> 32:47.269
-THERE IT IS.

33:09.509 --> 33:10.379
-HELLO?

33:11.815 --> 33:12.860
HELLO?

33:13.513 --> 33:14.731
CRAIG!

33:15.515 --> 33:16.559
APRIL!

33:16.690 --> 33:17.952
-J.D., CHECK THIS OUT.

33:19.693 --> 33:21.608
LOOKS LIKE THEY
WENT DOWN AT 2:47.

33:22.522 --> 33:24.132
IT'S ALMOST 6:00 NOW.

33:25.307 --> 33:26.874
THAT MEANS THEY'VE BEEN
DOWN ALMOST THREE HOURS.

33:27.005 --> 33:28.136
-THEY'LL NEVER SURVIVE.

33:30.573 --> 33:32.053
-BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS,
THIS IS NEWMAN

33:32.184 --> 33:33.272
ON RELENTLESS, COME IN.

33:35.622 --> 33:36.840
-YEAH, NEWMIE, I
READ YA, WHAT'S UP?

33:36.971 --> 33:38.929
-HIS BOAT'S EMPTY,
ACCORDING TO HIS LOG HE WENT

33:39.060 --> 33:42.107
DOWN AT 2:47 AT MAX
THE TANKS HE WAS USING

33:42.237 --> 33:43.630
PUT HIM ON BOTTOM
TIME AN HOUR,

33:43.760 --> 33:45.023
MAYBE AN HOUR AND 15.

33:45.762 --> 33:46.850
-GET DOWN THERE.

33:46.981 --> 33:47.764
-NEWMAN: WE'RE
ON OUR WAY.

33:51.942 --> 33:55.511
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

34:02.736 --> 34:04.433
-THERE'S NO WAY OUT
OF HERE, IS THERE?

34:04.564 --> 34:06.131
-LOOK, BY NOW EVERY
LIFEGUARD AT BAYWATCH

34:06.261 --> 34:07.654
IS SEARCHING FOR US AND
THEY'RE GONNA FIND US

34:07.784 --> 34:09.134
AND ALL WE GOTTA DO
IS HANG ON 'TIL THEN.

34:09.264 --> 34:10.744
-I DON'T KNOW IF I CAN.

34:10.873 --> 34:12.789
I MEAN EVERY TIME THAT
THING GOES ON AGAIN, I...

34:13.703 --> 34:15.879
-YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, I KNOW,
LOOK, IF IT GOES ON AGAIN,

34:16.010 --> 34:18.143
IT'S GONNA GO OFF AGAIN,
AND I GOTTA BELIEVE YOU CAN

34:18.273 --> 34:19.187
HANG ON, PROMISE ME.

34:19.840 --> 34:20.623
-I'LL TRY.

34:20.754 --> 34:22.060
-GOOD! GOOD.

34:23.713 --> 34:24.540
-CRAIG!

34:24.670 --> 34:26.194
-WHAT?

34:26.889 --> 34:27.891
-APRIL: OH.

34:28.588 --> 34:29.676
-CLIMB UP, HOLD ON,
HOLD ON, HOLD ON,

34:29.806 --> 34:30.981
TIGHT AS YOU CAN.

34:31.112 --> 34:32.373
OKAY, KEEP YOURSELF
OUT OF THE WATER.

34:32.940 --> 34:34.637
-I GOT HIM,
OKAY, COME ON.

34:34.768 --> 34:36.857
ALL RIGHT,
COME ON BUDDY!

34:36.987 --> 34:38.076
COME ON!
I'M YOUR MAN!

34:42.210 --> 34:43.690
-CRAIG, WATCH OUT!

34:43.820 --> 34:45.605
-COME TO THE LIGHT, I
GOT SOMETHING FOR YA.

34:51.350 --> 34:52.351
-YOU READY?

34:52.481 --> 34:53.873
-ALL SET.

35:03.405 --> 35:04.624
-CRAIG: I DON'T
SEE HIM.

35:04.754 --> 35:05.625
I'VE LOST THE SHARK!

35:05.755 --> 35:06.843
CAN YOU SEE HIM?

35:07.757 --> 35:09.542
-APRIL: NO, I DON'T
SEE HIM EITHER!

35:10.195 --> 35:14.112
-[SCUBA TANKS BUBBLING
AND BREATHING]

35:38.614 --> 35:40.050
-COME ON, BUDDY!

35:40.181 --> 35:41.356
COME TO ME!

35:44.925 --> 35:46.883
COME ON, THIS
WAY, THIS WAY!

35:48.929 --> 35:51.845
[GROANING AND STRAINING]

35:56.980 --> 36:00.723
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

36:17.262 --> 36:18.350
-COME ON, BUDDY!

36:18.480 --> 36:19.481
COME TO MY LIGHT!

36:19.612 --> 36:21.527
-[BUZZER SOUNDING]

36:22.745 --> 36:23.877
COME ON, THIS WAY!

36:25.618 --> 36:26.619
THIS WAY!

36:26.749 --> 36:27.533
COME TO ME!

36:27.663 --> 36:28.969
THIS WAY!

36:29.578 --> 36:30.753
-CRAIG!

36:30.884 --> 36:32.320
-COME ON!

36:32.451 --> 36:35.410
[STRAINING AND GROANING]

36:44.854 --> 36:45.812
AH!

36:53.036 --> 36:53.994
AH!

36:54.124 --> 36:55.865
-OH!

36:55.996 --> 36:58.564
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

37:06.180 --> 37:10.228
-[WATER GURGLING]

37:27.375 --> 37:28.507
-HOLD ON!

37:28.637 --> 37:29.943
BE POSITIVE!

37:30.726 --> 37:32.250
YOU JUST GOTTA HANG ON!

37:41.911 --> 37:43.565
LOOK, APRIL, LOOK!

37:44.827 --> 37:46.438
-APRIL: HOLD ON!

37:47.177 --> 37:48.962
-J.D.: CRAIG, HELP ME!

37:50.180 --> 37:51.573
HELP!

37:52.226 --> 37:53.096
CRAIG!

37:54.315 --> 37:55.708
HELP!

37:56.883 --> 37:58.188
-WHERE IN THE
HELL ARE YOU, MAN?

37:58.319 --> 37:59.494
WHERE IN THE HELL ARE YOU?

38:06.719 --> 38:08.808
-BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS
THIS IS SEA CAT, COME IN.

38:09.635 --> 38:11.245
-NEWMIE, IT'S MITCH,
WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

38:11.376 --> 38:12.942
-WE FOUND CRAIG'S SWIM FIN,
THEY'RE IN AN UNDERWATER

38:13.073 --> 38:15.423
GRATE, WE'RE TRYING TO GET
INSIDE, THERE WAS AN INCREDIBLY

38:15.554 --> 38:17.207
STRONG CURRENT THAT
SUCKED J.D. IN.

38:17.338 --> 38:19.427
-SOUNDS LIKE THEY'RE
IN THE INTAKE SYSTEM.

38:20.210 --> 38:21.560
RON, GET ME THE CONTROLLER
OF THE POWER PLANT

38:21.690 --> 38:22.517
ON THE LINE RIGHT AWAY.

38:22.648 --> 38:23.866
-RON: OKAY, MITCH.

38:25.564 --> 38:26.434
-J.D.: NO, CRAIG!

38:26.565 --> 38:27.783
LET GO!

38:28.697 --> 38:29.742
CRAIG!

38:37.184 --> 38:38.098
CRAIG!

38:38.228 --> 38:39.578
I'M SLIPPING!

38:46.454 --> 38:47.716
I'M SLIPPING!

38:48.326 --> 38:49.414
LET ME GO!
-CRAIG: NO!

38:49.544 --> 38:50.371
-YOU'LL BE PULLED IN, TOO!

38:50.502 --> 38:52.199
-IF YOU GO, WE GO!

38:53.809 --> 38:56.638
-[WATER RUSHING]

39:15.701 --> 39:17.659
-LIEUTENANT BUCHANAN,
L.A. COUNTY LIFEGUARDS,

39:17.790 --> 39:19.792
CAN YOU SHUT DOWN
THE POWER PLANT?

39:19.922 --> 39:20.706
-MAN: WHEN SIR,
WHEN ARE--

39:20.836 --> 39:22.316
-RIGHT NOW!

39:22.447 --> 39:23.361
THERE MAY BE SOMEBODY
IN THE INTAKE SYSTEM.

39:24.100 --> 39:24.927
-MAN: WAIT,
SIR, ARE YOU SERIOUS?

39:25.058 --> 39:26.276
IS IT POSSIBLE?

39:26.407 --> 39:27.626
-YES, I'M SERIOUS.
SHUT IT DOWN!

39:27.756 --> 39:28.409
-MAN: WELL IT'S
NOT THAT EASY, SIR.

39:28.540 --> 39:29.367
-SHUT IT DOWN!

39:31.194 --> 39:32.848
-HOLD ON, J.D.!

39:32.979 --> 39:35.373
-[GRUNTING AND GROANING]

39:40.465 --> 39:42.902
-[BUZZER SOUNDING]

39:43.032 --> 39:44.469
-[TURBINES SQUEAK]

39:52.999 --> 39:55.001
-[BUZZER CONTINUES]

39:56.698 --> 39:59.309
-LISTEN, IT STOPPED.

39:59.440 --> 40:01.399
THEY SHUT OFF THE MOTOR.
-[APRIL LAUGHS]

40:01.529 --> 40:03.226
-[J.D. LAUGHS]

40:04.706 --> 40:06.447
[PANTING]

40:09.798 --> 40:11.147
HOW MUCH AIR
YOU GOT IN THAT?

40:11.278 --> 40:13.715
-MORE THAN HALF.
-[APRIL LAUGHS]

40:15.195 --> 40:16.152
-CRAIG: SEE?

40:16.283 --> 40:17.458
WE'RE GETTIN'
OUT OF HERE.

40:17.589 --> 40:18.807
-J.D.: WE'RE
GOIN' HOME!

40:22.985 --> 40:23.899
-CRAIG: COME ON!

40:34.170 --> 40:35.694
-APRIL: THAT WAS
SO DELICIOUS.

40:35.824 --> 40:37.609
NEXT TIME I'M GONNA
MAKE DINNER FOR YOU.

40:37.739 --> 40:40.655
IT MIGHT NOT BE AS
GREAT, BUT I CAN MAKE MY

40:40.786 --> 40:42.962
MOM'S SPECIAL MEATLOAF
WITH BACON AND CHEESE.

40:44.398 --> 40:45.791
-HEY, THERE'S CRAIG!

40:46.574 --> 40:48.271
-WOULD YOU GUYS
EXCUSE ME A MINUTE?

40:48.402 --> 40:49.577
-ABSOLUTELY.

40:50.839 --> 40:52.014
-HEY.

40:52.145 --> 40:53.581
-HOW'S YOUR ARM DOING?

40:53.712 --> 40:55.235
-AH, IT'S FINE, JUST
A COUPLE OF STITCHES.

40:55.365 --> 40:56.584
-GOOD.

40:57.803 --> 40:59.065
LOOKS LIKE THINGS ARE
GOING BETTER BETWEEN

40:59.195 --> 41:00.109
YOU AND MANNY.

41:00.806 --> 41:01.937
IS THAT HIS MOM?

41:02.068 --> 41:03.896
-YEAH, SHE MADE
US A PICNIC.

41:04.026 --> 41:05.332
-THAT'S NICE.

41:06.072 --> 41:07.116
I'LL LET YOU GET
BACK TO IT.

41:07.682 --> 41:11.730
-UM, LISTEN, OKAY, I JUST
WANT TO SAY THANK YOU.

41:12.644 --> 41:14.472
I DON'T KNOW IF I WOULD'VE
SURVIVED WITHOUT YOU.

41:14.602 --> 41:16.996
-DON'T THANK ME, I'M THE ONE
THAT GOT US INTO THAT MESS.

41:17.126 --> 41:18.258
-TRUE.

41:18.867 --> 41:20.216
BUT YOU GOT US OUT.

41:20.347 --> 41:21.479
-SO WE'RE EVEN.

41:22.262 --> 41:23.393
-THANK YOU.

41:24.394 --> 41:25.657
-BETTER GET BACK
TO YOUR LUNCH.

41:27.049 --> 41:31.227
-[UPBEAT MUSIC]

41:32.185 --> 41:34.230
-APRIL: I AM NEVER GOING
DIVING WITH HIM AGAIN.

41:34.361 --> 41:36.406
-[ALL LAUGHING]

41:45.241 --> 41:49.637
-[END THEME PLAYING]
